<chapter id="ch-testing">
  <title>Testing</title>
  <section id="testing-types">
    <title>Types of Testing</title>
    <para>
      Testing deserves its own book but I'll keep testing information here
      until there is enough content.
    </para>

    <para>
      Nearly all the types of testing can be automated. There should be
      included in the source tree all the files that are needed for running
      automated testing. These should included project files, audio files
      and testing tools.
    </para>

    <para>
      There should be a 'test' build target that runs all tests
    </para>

    <variablelist>
      <title></title>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Unit Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The unit testing will be performed using the Boost test library.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>System Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            System testing involves testing to ensure that the requirements
            are met. A system test plan is needed.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Performance Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Latency
          </para>

          <para>
            Read and Write throughput
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Scalability Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Maximum Tracks
          </para>

          <para>
            Canvas
          </para>

          <para>
            Plugins
          </para>

          <para>
            Multi-core processing/overhead etc
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Regression Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Use System test plan
          </para>

          <para>
            Add Bug reports to system test plan
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Stress Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Simulate competition for resources such as memory, disk space
            and cpu time.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Smoke Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Core tests in system test plan
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Recovery Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Simulate crashes to test data recovery
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Installation Testing</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            tests to be preformed prior to release
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>

  <section id="test-framework">
    <title>Test Framework</title>
    <para></para>
  </section>

  <section id="code-coverage">
    <title>Code Coverage</title>
    <para></para>
  </section>
